                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-438" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HALL</persName>
                  </hi>. My partner's name is Samuel Hall—we live at No. 3, Leadenhall-street. We had a piece of kerseymere, which was safe on the evening of the 31st of January—I saw it lying exposed on the side Counter, within two yards of the door—I and my brother went to tea, leaving the shop with the porter or errand-boy—I can identify the cloth, which was found on the prisoner's person.</p>
